1. add()

Adds an element.

ArrayList<String> list = new ArrayList<>();

list.add("Java");
list.add("Python");

Output:

[Java, Python]
2. add(index, element)

Insert at specific position.

list.add(1, "C++");

Output:

[Java, C++, Python]
3. addAll()

Adds another collection.

ArrayList<String> list2 = new ArrayList<>();

list2.add("HTML");
list2.add("CSS");

list.addAll(list2);
4. get()

Retrieves element by index.

System.out.println(list.get(0));

Output:

Java
5. set()

Updates element.

list.set(1, "JavaScript");

Output:

[Java, JavaScript, Python]
6. remove(index)
list.remove(0);
7. remove(object)
list.remove("Python");
8. removeAll()

Remove all matching elements.

list.removeAll(list2);
9. contains()

Checks existence.

list.contains("Java");

Output:

true
10. indexOf()

Returns first occurrence index.

list.indexOf("Java");

Output:

0
11. lastIndexOf()

Returns last occurrence.

list.lastIndexOf("Java");
12. size()

Returns total elements.

list.size();
13. isEmpty()

Checks whether list is empty.

list.isEmpty();

Output:

false
14. clear()

Removes everything.

list.clear();

Output:

[]
15. sort()

Sort elements.

Collections.sort(list);

Before:

[Java, C, Python]

After:

[C, Java, Python]
16. clone()

Creates copy.

ArrayList<String> copy =
(ArrayList<String>) list.clone();
17. subList()

Creates a portion of list.

list.subList(1, 3);
18. toArray()

Converts ArrayList to Array.

Object[] arr = list.toArray();
19. retainAll()

Keeps only common elements.

list1.retainAll(list2);
20. Iterator()

Used for traversal.

Iterator<String> itr = list.iterator();

while(itr.hasNext()){
    System.out.println(itr.next());
}
